'''Janette Ahrens''' (born 1923) was an [[United States|American]] [[Figure skating|figure skater]].<ref name=twsJanK11>{{cite news |title= Figure Skating US National Championship Medalists |publisher= ''Go Figure Skating'' |quote= janette ahrens (silver medal: 1945, 1946, 1947) |year= 1945 |url= http://gofigureskating.com/people/usnationals.html |accessdate= 2010-01-11 }}</ref> She competed as both a single and [[pair skating|pair skater]], first with partner [[Robert Uppgren]] and later with [[Arthur Preusch]]. She also competed in fours with Uppgren, [[Mary Louise Premer]], and [[Lyman Wakefield, Jr.]] and won the 1941 [[North American Figure Skating Championships|North American title]].
